  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key components typically include:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\n2. Laws like the Bank Secrecy Act in the United States\n3. International standards set by the Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n4. Regulations covering banks, credit unions, investment firms, and other financial services\n\nThese regulations aim to detect and prevent financial crimes like money laundering, terrorist financing, and fraud.",
